		<section name="Other Methods">
			<p>
                This chapter will describe the set of utility methods available
                to services. These are methods not directly involved in the
                process of authentication, but may useful for services in other
                respects.
            </p>
            
            <subsection name="User Existence">
                <p>
					In order to check whether a certain user is visible in the
					Moria2 framework, services may use the following method.
					</p>
					<p>
					Method used by service: <code>verifyUserExistence</code>
					(<a href="moria-web/apidocs/no/feide/moria/webservices/v2_1/Authentication.html#verifyUserExistence(java.lang.String)">JavaDoc</a>, 
					<a href="howto_service_example_soap_verifyUserExistence.html">SOAP Example</a>, 
					<a href="howto_service_example_java-axis_verifyUserExistence.html">Java/Axis Example</a>)
			</p>
            </subsection>
			
		</section>
